= Kill Time Sample =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Removes all time samples from specified primitives, collapsing them to a single static value."""

== Overview ==

Kill Time Sample strips all time-sampled values from the selected primitives and replaces them with a single static value sampled at the specified frame. Use this to freeze animated primitives or to remove unwanted motion blur from specific objects.

@parameters

Primitives:
    #id: primitives
    USD primitives to remove time samples from.

Frame:
    #id: frame
    The frame at which to sample the current values before removing all other time samples. Defaults to `$F`.
